        "content": "\n\nB. Oxybutynin\n\nOxybutynin is an antimuscarinic agent used for urinary incontinence. In elderly patients, anticholinergic medications are a common cause of acute confusion and delirium due to their central nervous system effects. The other listed medications (metformin, lisinopril, metoprolol, hydrochlorothiazide) are far less likely to produce acute cognitive changes in this setting.",
